# orcasecurity_integration_monday_template (Resource)

Manages a [Monday.com](https://monday.com) template in Orca Security. The
template defines which Monday board / group Orca creates items in, how alert
fields map to Monday board columns, and how Monday status-column changes reflect
back as Orca alert state changes.

Credentials for Monday.com are stored on a separate Orca resource (OAuth). Create
the credentials side in the Orca UI, copy its UUID, and pass it in via the
`resource_id` argument.

Under the hood this creates an entry under `POST /api/external_service/config`
with `service_name = "monday"`. Updates go to
`PUT /api/external_service/config/monday?template=<template_name>`.

